## ZSH shared memory

This project uses a shared, agent-independent memory system.

Before resuming previous work:

1. Read `AGENT_MEMORY.md`.
2. Follow its context reconstruction protocol.
3. Treat `skill-docs/CURRENT_TASK.md` as the authoritative persisted work state.
4. Do not infer historical progress before reading the memory files.
5. At the end of a work session, follow the write-back protocol in `AGENT_MEMORY.md`.

If a referenced memory file is missing or inconsistent, report the problem instead of inventing context.

ZSH project memory is authoritative over agent-native memory. Before ending the session, incrementally write back verified project facts; skip duplicates and ask before resolving conflicts.
